body:
### Describe the bug

Cython with type annotated  Python functions with object memoryviews generates code with unused functions, creating compiler warnings. 

### Code to reproduce the behaviour:

This is an example of a Cython file to reproduce the problem.
```cython
# t.pyx
def foo(obj_memview: object[:]):
    for i in range(len(obj_memview)):
        print(obj_memview[i])
```

Transpiling with `cython t.pyx`, then compiling with

```bash
gcc t.c -Wall -Wextra -I /usr/include/python3.14/ -lpython3.14 -shared -fPIC
```

generates this warnings:

```
t.c:24957:14: warning: ‘__pyx_memview_set_object’ defined but not used [-Wunused-function]
24957 |   static int __pyx_memview_set_object(const char *itemp, PyObject *obj) {
      |              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
t.c:24952:20: warning: ‘__pyx_memview_get_object’ defined but not used [-Wunused-function]
24952 |   static PyObject *__pyx_memview_get_object(const char *itemp) {
      |                    ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
```

### Expected behaviour

No unused function on the generated code.

### OS

Linux

### Python version

Cython installed in 3.13.9; code compiled against Python 3.14.2

### Cython version

3.2.4

### Additional context

This issue was discovered in https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/pull/63726. The warning occurred in functions type annotated with `arr: object[:]` and `object[:] keys`.
title: [BUG] Cython generates C code with unused function with object memoryview
